    "solution": "Presence of strong base (EtO<sup>-</sup>) and heat indicates elimination.<br><br>\nThus, the compound undergoes dehydrohalogenation, and alkene is produced. As per the position of <b>Cl</b> in\nsubstrate, the following 2 alkenes are formed as product:<br><br>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l2r5jmna/d7a63218-67e4-47d9-9e4b-4ca2e948bb89/e5c34950-cb6c-11ec-9b8a-d5d80e93637e/file-1l2r5jmnb.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l2r5jmna/d7a63218-67e4-47d9-9e4b-4ca2e948bb89/e5c34950-cb6c-11ec-9b8a-d5d80e93637e/file-1l2r5jmnb.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 12th January Evening Slot Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 139 English Explanation 1\"><br><br>\nIn accordance with Saytzeff rule<br><br>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l2r5l1oa/3e9ecad4-1701-4be2-b55f-140177fcedad/0d2e61a0-cb6d-11ec-9b8a-d5d80e93637e/file-1l2r5l1ob.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l2r5l1oa/3e9ecad4-1701-4be2-b55f-140177fcedad/0d2e61a0-cb6d-11ec-9b8a-d5d80e93637e/file-1l2r5l1ob.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 12th January Evening Slot Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 139 English Explanation 2\"><br><br>\nwill be the major product.",
