    "options": [],
    "solution": "(1) The structure of 3-bromo-3-cyclopentylhexane -\n<br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lh4qs3bg/37084bb5-0302-4e8b-b01b-48367402ea9e/2892f0c0-e811-11ed-8e58-b75ca46f959b/file-1lh4qs3bh.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lh4qs3bg/37084bb5-0302-4e8b-b01b-48367402ea9e/2892f0c0-e811-11ed-8e58-b75ca46f959b/file-1lh4qs3bh.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2011 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 16 English Explanation 1\">\n<br><br>(2) Since, bromide (Br<sup>–</sup>) is a good leaving group,\nelimination using strong base takes place using\nstrong base (KOH) take via E<sub>2</sub> mechanism.\nThis is also called $$\\beta $$ elimination.\n<br><br>(3) There are 3 different types of protons :\n<br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lh4qwq76/7ba176d5-e6fd-4c54-81a0-df91096373ea/a97c5820-e811-11ed-8e58-b75ca46f959b/file-1lh4qwq77.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lh4qwq76/7ba176d5-e6fd-4c54-81a0-df91096373ea/a97c5820-e811-11ed-8e58-b75ca46f959b/file-1lh4qwq77.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2011 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 16 English Explanation 2\">\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lh4qxag3/12d885f1-5807-409f-bc6c-f2278b7a3b34/b9206730-e811-11ed-a20e-7175d6544f78/file-1lh4qxag4.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lh4qxag3/12d885f1-5807-409f-bc6c-f2278b7a3b34/b9206730-e811-11ed-a20e-7175d6544f78/file-1lh4qxag4.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2011 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 16 English Explanation 3\">\n<br><br>(iv) The strong base abstracts $$\\beta $$ hydrogen (H<sub>1</sub> or H<sub>2</sub>\nor H<sub>3</sub>) with simultaneous loss of bromide ion\nforming an alkene. This alkene can exist in 2\nconformations, E and Z.\n<br><br>(a) Elimination of H<sub>1</sub> proton :\n<br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lh4r3s85/39113a58-98f9-4cce-bcf7-ba9761164699/6db72d50-e812-11ed-a20e-7175d6544f78/file-1lh4r3s86.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lh4r3s85/39113a58-98f9-4cce-bcf7-ba9761164699/6db72d50-e812-11ed-a20e-7175d6544f78/file-1lh4r3s86.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2011 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 16 English Explanation 4\">\n<br><br>This product can exist in 2\nconformations, E and Z.\n<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lh4rm8vw/f69a5079-106b-4f8b-a5e6-1ec6824c0f8e/6f2662d0-e814-11ed-a20e-7175d6544f78/file-1lh4rm8vx.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lh4rm8vw/f69a5079-106b-4f8b-a5e6-1ec6824c0f8e/6f2662d0-e814-11ed-a20e-7175d6544f78/file-1lh4rm8vx.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2011 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 16 English Explanation 5\">\n<br><br>(b) Elimination of H<sub>2</sub> proton :\n<br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lh4rc1at/91c0d433-1dcf-43e1-ba4d-49811fe610dc/5332bc50-e813-11ed-a20e-7175d6544f78/file-1lh4rc1au.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lh4rc1at/91c0d433-1dcf-43e1-ba4d-49811fe610dc/5332bc50-e813-11ed-a20e-7175d6544f78/file-1lh4rc1au.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2011 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 16 English Explanation 6\">\n<br><br>Since, the groups about sp<sup>2</sup>\n hybridised carbon\nof cyclopentane is fixed no E and Z forms\nare possible. This molecule has only one\nconformation.\n<br><br>(c) Elimination of H<sub>3</sub> proton :\n<br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lh4rh9o5/0dc336ac-0f3d-469f-8180-f0c95f74ed50/e4b5b650-e813-11ed-a20e-7175d6544f78/file-1lh4rh9o6.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lh4rh9o5/0dc336ac-0f3d-469f-8180-f0c95f74ed50/e4b5b650-e813-11ed-a20e-7175d6544f78/file-1lh4rh9o6.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2011 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 16 English Explanation 7\">\n<br><br>This product can exist in 2\nconformations, E and Z.\n<br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lh4r8ect/d05f8eba-7b95-45f0-9332-ce77ba9a2e86/ee0bf5d0-e812-11ed-a20e-7175d6544f78/file-1lh4r8ecu.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lh4r8ect/d05f8eba-7b95-45f0-9332-ce77ba9a2e86/ee0bf5d0-e812-11ed-a20e-7175d6544f78/file-1lh4r8ecu.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2011 Paper 1 Offline Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 16 English Explanation 8\">\n<br><br>Hence, a total of 5 products are possible.",
